{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Is there anything unique about human beings?"},{"time":3000,"text":"There is."},{"time":5000,"text":"We're the only creatures"},{"time":7000,"text":"with fully developed moral sentiments."},{"time":9000,"text":"We're obsessed with morality as social creatures."},{"time":12000,"text":"We need to know why people are doing what they're doing."},{"time":15000,"text":"And I personally am obsessed with morality."},{"time":18000,"text":"It was all due to this woman,"},{"time":20000,"text":"Sister Mary Marastela,"},{"time":22000,"text":"also known as my mom."},{"time":26000,"text":"As an altar boy, I breathed in a lot of incense,"},{"time":29000,"text":"and I learned to say phrases in Latin,"},{"time":31000,"text":"but I also had time to think"},{"time":33000,"text":"about whether my mother's top-down morality"},{"time":35000,"text":"applied to everybody."},{"time":37000,"text":"I saw that people who were religious and non-religious"},{"time":40000,"text":"were equally obsessed with morality."},{"time":42000,"text":"I thought, maybe there's some earthly basis"},{"time":44000,"text":"for moral decisions."},{"time":46000,"text":"But I wanted to go further"},{"time":48000,"text":"than to say our brains make us moral."},{"time":50000,"text":"I want to know if there's a chemistry of morality."},{"time":53000,"text":"I want to know"},{"time":55000,"text":"if there was a moral molecule."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57000,"text":"After 10 years of experiments,"},{"time":59000,"text":"I found it."},{"time":61000,"text":"Would you like to see it? I brought some with me."},{"time":65000,"text":"This little syringe"},{"time":67000,"text":"contains the moral molecule."},{"time":76000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":79000,"text":"It's called oxytocin."},{"time":81000,"text":"So oxytocin is a simple and ancient molecule"},{"time":84000,"text":"found only in mammals."},{"time":86000,"text":"In rodents, it was known"},{"time":88000,"text":"to make mothers care for their offspring,"},{"time":90000,"text":"and in some creatures,"},{"time":92000,"text":"allowed for toleration of burrowmates."},{"time":94000,"text":"But in humans, it was only known"},{"time":96000,"text":"to facilitate birth and breastfeeding in women,"},{"time":98000,"text":"and is released by both sexes during sex."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"So I had this idea that oxytocin might be the moral molecule."},{"time":105000,"text":"I did what most of us do -- I tried it on some colleagues."},{"time":108000,"text":"One of them told me,"},{"time":110000,"text":"\"Paul, that is the world's stupidist idea."},{"time":113000,"text":"It is,\" he said, \"only a female molecule."},{"time":115000,"text":"It can't be that important.\""},{"time":117000,"text":"But I countered, \"Well men's brains make this too."},{"time":120000,"text":"There must be a reason why.\""},{"time":122000,"text":"But he was right, it was a stupid idea."},{"time":125000,"text":"But it was testably stupid."},{"time":127000,"text":"In other words, I thought I could design an experiment"},{"time":130000,"text":"to see if oxytocin made people moral."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"Turns out it wasn't so easy."},{"time":136000,"text":"First of all, oxytocin is a shy molecule."},{"time":139000,"text":"Baseline levels are near zero,"},{"time":141000,"text":"without some stimulus to cause its release."},{"time":144000,"text":"And when it's produced, it has a three-minute half-life,"},{"time":146000,"text":"and degrades rapidly at room temperature."},{"time":149000,"text":"So this experiment would have to cause a surge of oxytocin,"},{"time":151000,"text":"have to grab it fast and keep it cold."},{"time":153000,"text":"I think I can do that."},{"time":155000,"text":"Now luckily, oxytocin is produced"},{"time":157000,"text":"both in the brain and in the blood,"},{"time":160000,"text":"so I could do this experiment without learning neurosurgery."},{"time":164000,"text":"Then I had to measure morality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"So taking on Morality with a capital M is a huge project."},{"time":170000,"text":"So I started smaller."},{"time":172000,"text":"I studied one single virtue:"},{"time":175000,"text":"trustworthiness."},{"time":177000,"text":"Why? I had shown in the early 2000s"},{"time":180000,"text":"that countries with a higher proportion of trustworthy people"},{"time":183000,"text":"are more prosperous."},{"time":185000,"text":"So in these countries, more economic transactions occur"},{"time":188000,"text":"and more wealth is created,"},{"time":190000,"text":"alleviating poverty."},{"time":192000,"text":"So poor countries are by and large low trust countries."},{"time":195000,"text":"So if I understood the chemistry of trustworthiness,"},{"time":198000,"text":"I might help alleviate poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"But I'm also a skeptic."},{"time":202000,"text":"I don't want to just ask people, \"Are you trustworthy?\""},{"time":204000,"text":"So instead I use"},{"time":206000,"text":"the Jerry Maguire approach to research."},{"time":208000,"text":"If you're so virtuous,"},{"time":210000,"text":"show me the money."},{"time":212000,"text":"So what we do in my lab"},{"time":214000,"text":"is we tempt people with virtue and vice by using money."},{"time":216000,"text":"Let me show you how we do that."},{"time":218000,"text":"So we recruit some people for an experiment."},{"time":220000,"text":"They all get $10 if they agree to show up."},{"time":223000,"text":"We give them lots of instruction, and we never ever deceive them."},{"time":226000,"text":"Then we match them in pairs by computer."},{"time":229000,"text":"And in that pair, one person gets a message saying,"},{"time":231000,"text":"\"Do you want to give up some of your $10"},{"time":233000,"text":"you earned for being here"},{"time":235000,"text":"and ship it to someone else in the lab?\""},{"time":237000,"text":"The trick is you can't see them,"},{"time":239000,"text":"you can't talk to them."},{"time":241000,"text":"You only do it one time."},{"time":243000,"text":"Now whatever you give up"},{"time":245000,"text":"gets tripled in the other person's account."},{"time":248000,"text":"You're going to make them a lot wealthier."},{"time":250000,"text":"And they get a message by computer saying"},{"time":252000,"text":"person one sent you this amount of money."},{"time":254000,"text":"Do you want to keep it all,"},{"time":256000,"text":"or do you want to send some amount back?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"So think about this experiment for minute."},{"time":261000,"text":"You're going to sit on these hard chairs for an hour and a half."},{"time":264000,"text":"Some mad scientist is going to jab your arm with a needle"},{"time":266000,"text":"and take four tubes of blood."},{"time":268000,"text":"And now you want me to give up this money and ship it to a stranger?"},{"time":271000,"text":"So this was the birth of vampire economics."},{"time":274000,"text":"Make a decision and give me some blood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277000,"text":"So in fact, experimental economists"},{"time":279000,"text":"had run this test around the world,"},{"time":281000,"text":"and for much higher stakes,"},{"time":283000,"text":"and the consensus view"},{"time":285000,"text":"was that the measure from the first person to the second was a measure of trust,"},{"time":288000,"text":"and the transfer from the second person back to the first"},{"time":291000,"text":"measured trustworthiness."},{"time":293000,"text":"But in fact, economists were flummoxed"},{"time":295000,"text":"on why the second person would ever return any money."},{"time":298000,"text":"They assumed money is good,"},{"time":300000,"text":"why not keep it all?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"That's not what we found."},{"time":304000,"text":"We found 90 percent of the first decision-makers sent money,"},{"time":307000,"text":"and of those who received money,"},{"time":309000,"text":"95 percent returned some of it."},{"time":311000,"text":"But why?"},{"time":313000,"text":"Well by measuring oxytocin"},{"time":315000,"text":"we found that the more money the second person received,"},{"time":317000,"text":"the more their brain produced oxytocin,"},{"time":319000,"text":"and the more oxytocin on board,"},{"time":321000,"text":"the more money they returned."},{"time":324000,"text":"So we have a biology of trustworthiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327000,"text":"But wait. What's wrong with this experiment?"},{"time":330000,"text":"Two things."},{"time":332000,"text":"One is that nothing in the body happens in isolation."},{"time":335000,"text":"So we measured nine other molecules that interact with oxytocin,"},{"time":338000,"text":"but they didn't have any effect."},{"time":340000,"text":"But the second is"},{"time":342000,"text":"that I still only had this indirect relationship"},{"time":344000,"text":"between oxytocin and trustworthiness."},{"time":346000,"text":"I didn't know for sure"},{"time":348000,"text":"oxytocin caused trustworthiness."},{"time":350000,"text":"So to make the experiment,"},{"time":352000,"text":"I knew I'd have to go into the brain"},{"time":354000,"text":"and manipulate oxytocin directly."},{"time":356000,"text":"I used everything short of a drill"},{"time":358000,"text":"to get oxytocin into my own brain."},{"time":361000,"text":"And I found I could do it"},{"time":363000,"text":"with a nasal inhaler."},{"time":365000,"text":"So along with colleagues in Zurich,"},{"time":367000,"text":"we put 200 men on oxytocin or placebo,"},{"time":369000,"text":"had that same trust test with money,"},{"time":371000,"text":"and we found that those on oxytocin not only showed more trust,"},{"time":374000,"text":"we can more than double the number of people"},{"time":377000,"text":"who sent all their money to a stranger --"},{"time":379000,"text":"all without altering mood or cognition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383000,"text":"So oxytocin is the trust molecule,"},{"time":387000,"text":"but is it the moral molecule?"},{"time":390000,"text":"Using the oxytocin inhaler,"},{"time":392000,"text":"we ran more studies."},{"time":394000,"text":"We showed that oxytocin infusion"},{"time":396000,"text":"increases generosity"},{"time":398000,"text":"in unilateral monetary transfers"},{"time":400000,"text":"by 80 percent."},{"time":402000,"text":"We showed it increases donations to charity"},{"time":404000,"text":"by 50 percent."},{"time":406000,"text":"We've also investigated"},{"time":408000,"text":"non-pharmacologic ways to raise oxytocin."},{"time":410000,"text":"These include massage,"},{"time":412000,"text":"dancing and praying."},{"time":414000,"text":"Yes, my mom was happy about that last one."},{"time":417000,"text":"And whenever we raise oxytocin,"},{"time":419000,"text":"people willingly open up their wallets"},{"time":421000,"text":"and share money with strangers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"But why do they do this?"},{"time":425000,"text":"What does it feel like"},{"time":427000,"text":"when your brain is flooded with oxytocin?"},{"time":429000,"text":"To investigate this question, we ran an experiment"},{"time":432000,"text":"where we had people watch a video"},{"time":434000,"text":"of a father and his four year-old son,"},{"time":436000,"text":"and his son has terminal brain cancer."},{"time":438000,"text":"After they watched the video, we had them rate their feelings"},{"time":441000,"text":"and took blood before and after to measure oxytocin."},{"time":444000,"text":"The change in oxytocin"},{"time":446000,"text":"predicted their feelings of empathy."},{"time":450000,"text":"So it's empathy"},{"time":452000,"text":"that makes us connect to other people."},{"time":454000,"text":"It's empathy that makes us help other people."},{"time":457000,"text":"It's empathy that makes us moral."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461000,"text":"Now this idea is not new."},{"time":463000,"text":"A then unknown philosopher named Adam Smith"},{"time":465000,"text":"wrote a book in 1759"},{"time":467000,"text":"called \"The Theory of Moral Sentiments.\""},{"time":469000,"text":"In this book, Smith argued"},{"time":472000,"text":"that we are moral creatures, not because of a top-down reason,"},{"time":475000,"text":"but for a bottom-up reason."},{"time":477000,"text":"He said we're social creatures,"},{"time":479000,"text":"so we share the emotions of others."},{"time":481000,"text":"So if I do something that hurts you, I feel that pain."},{"time":484000,"text":"So I tend to avoid that."},{"time":486000,"text":"If I do something that makes you happy, I get to share your joy."},{"time":489000,"text":"So I tend to do those things."},{"time":491000,"text":"Now this is the same Adam Smith who, 17 years later,"},{"time":493000,"text":"would write a little book called \"The Wealth of Nations\" --"},{"time":496000,"text":"the founding document of economics."},{"time":498000,"text":"But he was, in fact, a moral philosopher,"},{"time":501000,"text":"and he was right on why we're moral."},{"time":503000,"text":"I just found the molecule behind it."},{"time":506000,"text":"But knowing that molecule is valuable,"},{"time":509000,"text":"because it tells us how to turn up this behavior"},{"time":512000,"text":"and what turns it off."},{"time":514000,"text":"In particular, it tells us"},{"time":516000,"text":"why we see immorality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"So to investigate immorality,"},{"time":521000,"text":"let me bring you back now to 1980."},{"time":523000,"text":"I'm working at a gas station"},{"time":525000,"text":"on the outskirts of Santa Barbara, California."},{"time":528000,"text":"You sit in a gas station all day,"},{"time":530000,"text":"you see lots of morality and immorality, let me tell you."},{"time":532000,"text":"So one Sunday afternoon, a man walks into my cashier's booth"},{"time":535000,"text":"with this beautiful jewelry box."},{"time":537000,"text":"Opens it up and there's a pearl necklace inside."},{"time":539000,"text":"And he said, \"Hey, I was in the men's room."},{"time":541000,"text":"I just found this. What do you think we should do with it?\""},{"time":544000,"text":"\"I don't know, put it in the lost and found.\""},{"time":546000,"text":"\"Well this is very valuable."},{"time":548000,"text":"We have to find the owner for this.\" I said, \"Yea.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":550000,"text":"So we're trying to decide what to do with this,"},{"time":552000,"text":"and the phone rings."},{"time":554000,"text":"And a man says very excitedly,"},{"time":556000,"text":"\"I was in your gas station a while ago,"},{"time":558000,"text":"and I bought this jewelry for my wife, and I can't find it.\""},{"time":560000,"text":"I said, \"Pearl necklace?\" \"Yeah.\""},{"time":562000,"text":"\"Hey, a guy just found it.\""},{"time":564000,"text":"\"Oh, you're saving my life. Here's my phone number."},{"time":566000,"text":"Tell that guy to wait half an hour."},{"time":568000,"text":"I'll be there and I'll give him a $200 reward.\""},{"time":570000,"text":"Great, so I tell the guy, \"Look, relax."},{"time":572000,"text":"Get yourself a fat reward. Life's good.\""},{"time":575000,"text":"He said, \"I can't do it."},{"time":577000,"text":"I have this job interview in Galena in 15 minutes,"},{"time":579000,"text":"and I need this job, I've got to go.\""},{"time":582000,"text":"Again he asked me, \"What do you think we should do?\""},{"time":584000,"text":"I'm in high school. I have no idea."},{"time":587000,"text":"So I said, \"I'll hold it for you.\""},{"time":589000,"text":"He said, \"You know, you've been so nice, let's split the reward.\""},{"time":592000,"text":"I'll give you the jewelry, you give me a hundred dollars,"},{"time":594000,"text":"and when the guy comes ... \""}]},{"cues":[{"time":596000,"text":"You see it. I was conned."},{"time":598000,"text":"So this is a classic con called the pigeon drop,"},{"time":601000,"text":"and I was the pigeon."},{"time":603000,"text":"So the way many cons work"},{"time":605000,"text":"is not that the conman gets the victim to trust him,"},{"time":608000,"text":"it's that he shows he trusts the victim."},{"time":611000,"text":"Now we know what happens."},{"time":613000,"text":"The victim's brain releases oxytocin,"},{"time":615000,"text":"and you're opening up your wallet or purse, giving away the money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618000,"text":"So who are these people"},{"time":620000,"text":"who manipulate our oxytocin systems?"},{"time":623000,"text":"We found, testing thousands of individuals,"},{"time":626000,"text":"that five percent of the population"},{"time":628000,"text":"don't release oxytocin on stimulus."},{"time":632000,"text":"So if you trust them, their brains don't release oxytocin."},{"time":635000,"text":"If there's money on the table, they keep it all."},{"time":638000,"text":"So there's a technical word for these people in my lab."},{"time":640000,"text":"We call them bastards."},{"time":643000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":645000,"text":"These are not people you want to have a beer with."},{"time":647000,"text":"They have many of the attributes of psychopaths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651000,"text":"Now there are other ways the system can be inhibited."},{"time":653000,"text":"One is through improper nurturing."},{"time":656000,"text":"So we've studied sexually abused women,"},{"time":659000,"text":"and about half those don't release oxytocin on stimulus."},{"time":662000,"text":"You need enough nurturing"},{"time":664000,"text":"for this system to develop properly."},{"time":666000,"text":"Also, high stress inhibits oxytocin."},{"time":669000,"text":"So we all know this, when we're really stressed out,"},{"time":671000,"text":"we're not acting our best."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674000,"text":"There's another way oxytocin is inhibited, which is interesting --"},{"time":677000,"text":"through the action of testosterone."},{"time":680000,"text":"So we, in experiments, have administered testosterone to men."},{"time":683000,"text":"And instead of sharing money,"},{"time":685000,"text":"they become selfish."},{"time":687000,"text":"But interestingly,"},{"time":690000,"text":"high testosterone males are also more likely"},{"time":692000,"text":"to use their own money to punish others for being selfish."},{"time":695000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":697000,"text":"Now think about this. It means, within our own biology,"},{"time":700000,"text":"we have the yin and yang of morality."},{"time":703000,"text":"We have oxytocin that connects us to others,"},{"time":705000,"text":"makes us feel what they feel."},{"time":707000,"text":"And we have testosterone."},{"time":709000,"text":"And men have 10 times the testosterone as women,"},{"time":711000,"text":"so men do this more than women --"},{"time":713000,"text":"we have testosterone that makes us want to punish"},{"time":716000,"text":"people who behave immorally."},{"time":718000,"text":"We don't need God or government telling us what to do."},{"time":720000,"text":"It's all inside of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723000,"text":"So you may be wondering:"},{"time":725000,"text":"these are beautiful laboratory experiments,"},{"time":727000,"text":"do they really apply to real life?"},{"time":729000,"text":"Yeah, I've been worrying about that too."},{"time":731000,"text":"So I've gone out of the lab"},{"time":733000,"text":"to see if this really holds in our daily lives."},{"time":735000,"text":"So last summer, I attended a wedding in Southern England."},{"time":738000,"text":"200 people in this beautiful Victorian mansion."},{"time":741000,"text":"I didn't know a single person."},{"time":743000,"text":"And I drove up in my rented Vauxhall."},{"time":745000,"text":"And I took out a centrifuge and dry ice"},{"time":747000,"text":"and needles and tubes."},{"time":749000,"text":"And I took blood from the bride and the groom"},{"time":751000,"text":"and the wedding party and the family and the friends"},{"time":753000,"text":"before and immediately after the vows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":757000,"text":"And guess what?"},{"time":759000,"text":"Weddings cause a release of oxytocin,"},{"time":761000,"text":"but they do so in a very particular way."},{"time":764000,"text":"Who is the center of the wedding solar system?"},{"time":766000,"text":"The bride."},{"time":768000,"text":"She had the biggest increase in oxytocin."},{"time":770000,"text":"Who loves the wedding almost as much as the bride?"},{"time":773000,"text":"Her mother, that's right."},{"time":775000,"text":"Her mother was number two."},{"time":777000,"text":"Then the groom's father, then the groom,"},{"time":779000,"text":"then the family, then the friends --"},{"time":781000,"text":"arrayed around the bride"},{"time":783000,"text":"like planets around the Sun."},{"time":785000,"text":"So I think it tells us that we've designed this ritual"},{"time":788000,"text":"to connect us to this new couple,"},{"time":790000,"text":"connect us emotionally."},{"time":792000,"text":"Why? Because we need them to be successful at reproducing"},{"time":795000,"text":"to perpetuate the species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798000,"text":"I also worried that my trust experiments with small amounts of money"},{"time":801000,"text":"didn't really capture how often we actually trust our lives to strangers."},{"time":805000,"text":"So even though I have a fear of heights,"},{"time":807000,"text":"I recently strapped myself to another human being"},{"time":809000,"text":"and stepped out of an airplane at 12,000 ft."},{"time":812000,"text":"I took my blood before and after,"},{"time":814000,"text":"and I had a huge spike of oxytocin."},{"time":817000,"text":"And there are so many ways we can connect to people."},{"time":820000,"text":"For example, through social media."},{"time":822000,"text":"Many people are Tweeting right now."},{"time":824000,"text":"So we investigated the role of social media"},{"time":826000,"text":"and found the using social media"},{"time":828000,"text":"produced a solid double-digit increase in oxytocin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831000,"text":"So I ran this experiment recently for the Korean Broadcasting System."},{"time":834000,"text":"And they had the reporters and their producers participate."},{"time":838000,"text":"And one of these guys, he must have been 22,"},{"time":840000,"text":"he had 150 percent spike in oxytocin."},{"time":843000,"text":"I mean, astounding; no one has this."},{"time":845000,"text":"So he was using social media in private."},{"time":847000,"text":"When I wrote my report to the Koreans,"},{"time":849000,"text":"I said, \"Look, I don't know what this guy was doing,\""},{"time":851000,"text":"but my guess was interacting with his mother or his girlfriend."},{"time":854000,"text":"They checked."},{"time":856000,"text":"He was interacting on his girlfriend's Facebook page."},{"time":858000,"text":"There you go. That's connection."},{"time":861000,"text":"So there's tons of ways that we can connect to other people,"},{"time":864000,"text":"and it seems to be universal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866000,"text":"Two weeks ago,"},{"time":868000,"text":"I just got back from Papua New Guinea"},{"time":870000,"text":"where I went up to the highlands --"},{"time":872000,"text":"very isolated tribes of subsistence farmers"},{"time":875000,"text":"living as they have lived for millenia."},{"time":878000,"text":"There are 800 different languages in the highlands."},{"time":881000,"text":"These are the most primitive people in the world."},{"time":884000,"text":"And they indeed also release oxytocin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"So oxytocin connects us to other people."},{"time":891000,"text":"Oxytocin makes us feel what other people feel."},{"time":893000,"text":"And it's so easy to cause people's brains"},{"time":896000,"text":"to release oxytocin."},{"time":898000,"text":"I know how to do it,"},{"time":900000,"text":"and my favorite way to do it is, in fact, the easiest."},{"time":902000,"text":"Let me show it to you."},{"time":909000,"text":"Come here. Give me a hug."},{"time":911000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":913000,"text":"There you go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":924000,"text":"So my penchant for hugging other people"},{"time":926000,"text":"has earned me the nickname Dr. Love."},{"time":928000,"text":"I'm happy to share a little more love in the world,"},{"time":930000,"text":"it's great,"},{"time":932000,"text":"but here's your prescription from Dr. Love:"},{"time":934000,"text":"eight hugs a day."},{"time":937000,"text":"We have found that people who release more oxytocin"},{"time":939000,"text":"are happier."},{"time":941000,"text":"And they're happier"},{"time":943000,"text":"because they have better relationships of all types."},{"time":946000,"text":"Dr. Love says eight hugs a day."},{"time":949000,"text":"Eight hugs a day -- you'll be happier"},{"time":951000,"text":"and the world will be a better place."},{"time":953000,"text":"Of course, if you don't like to touch people, I can always shove this up your nose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":956000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":958000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}